<subSubSection id="D6B9258EC61BFFEA2A9C9A96371E7FF1" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9E1C7605C61BFFEA2A9C9A96371E7FF1" blockId="111.[151,1437,1476,2005]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C61BFFEA2A9C9A9632037CBC" bold="true" box="[151,273,1476,1501]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Easily distinguished from most congeners by subdistal lateral constriction of male chelicerae (
<figureCitation id="06986A80C61BFFEA2F649A9633D47F61" captionStart="FIGURES 489–493" captionStartId="112.[151,264,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,301,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@112.[151,1436,301,1889]" captionTargetPageId="112" captionText="FIGURES 489–493. Mesabolivar saci sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19207). 489–490. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 491. Left procursus, dorsal view. 492–493. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. Scale lines: 0.5 (489–490), 0.3 (491– 493)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202639/files/figure.png" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Fig. 492</figureCitation>
); also by details of male palp (procursus S-shaped in dorsal view, 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C61BFFEA29BD9AB5370A7F61" box="[950,1048,1511,1536]" captionStart="FIGURES 489–493" captionStartId="112.[151,264,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,301,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@112.[151,1436,301,1889]" captionTargetPageId="112" captionText="FIGURES 489–493. Mesabolivar saci sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19207). 489–490. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 491. Left procursus, dorsal view. 492–493. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. Scale lines: 0.5 (489–490), 0.3 (491– 493)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202639/files/figure.png" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Fig. 491</figureCitation>
; femur very large relative to tibia, 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C61BFFEA2A9C995E322B7F45" box="[151,313,1548,1573]" captionStart="FIGURES 489–493" captionStartId="112.[151,264,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,301,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@112.[151,1436,301,1889]" captionTargetPageId="112" captionText="FIGURES 489–493. Mesabolivar saci sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19207). 489–490. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 491. Left procursus, dorsal view. 492–493. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. Scale lines: 0.5 (489–490), 0.3 (491– 493)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202639/files/figure.png" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Figs 489–490</figureCitation>
), and by shape of epigynum (
<figureCitation id="06986A80C61BFFEA2897995E302C7F44" box="[668,830,1548,1573]" captionStart="FIGURES 494–497" captionStartId="113.[151,264,1248,1270]" captionTargetBox="[183,1408,207,1218]" captionTargetId="figure@113.[151,1436,193,1227]" captionTargetPageId="113" captionText="FIGURES 494–497. Mesabolivar saci sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19207). 494–496. Epigynum, ventral, lateral, and frontal views. 497. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines:0.3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202641/files/figure.png" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Figs 494–496</figureCitation>
; anterior plate with pair of large processes, median pocket, and small median anterior process); from the very similar 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C61BFFEA29709963370E7F29" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[891,1052,1585,1608]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constrictus">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C61BFFEA29709963370E7F29" box="[891,1052,1585,1608]" italics="true" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">M. constrictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by tip of procursus in dorsal view (compare 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C61BFFEA2B039906327E7F0D" box="[264,364,1620,1645]" captionStart="FIGURES 489–493" captionStartId="112.[151,264,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,301,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@112.[151,1436,301,1889]" captionTargetPageId="112" captionText="FIGURES 489–493. Mesabolivar saci sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19207). 489–490. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 491. Left procursus, dorsal view. 492–493. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. Scale lines: 0.5 (489–490), 0.3 (491– 493)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202639/files/figure.png" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Figs 491</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C61BFFEA2B72990632B57F0D" box="[377,423,1620,1644]" captionStart="FIGURES 498–505" captionStartId="115.[151,264,1833,1855]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,195,1809]" captionTargetId="figure@115.[151,1436,193,1812]" captionTargetPageId="115" captionText="FIGURES 498–505. Mesabolivar constrictus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19208). 498, 500. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 499. Left procursus, dorsal view. 501–504. Epigynum, ventral, posterior, frontal, and lateral views. 505. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines:0.3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202643/files/figure.png" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">499</figureCitation>
), by proximal anterior processes on male chelicerae (compare 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C61BFFEA2E61990637DD7F0D" box="[1130,1231,1620,1645]" captionStart="FIGURES 489–493" captionStartId="112.[151,264,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,301,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@112.[151,1436,301,1889]" captionTargetPageId="112" captionText="FIGURES 489–493. Mesabolivar saci sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19207). 489–490. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 491. Left procursus, dorsal view. 492–493. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. Scale lines: 0.5 (489–490), 0.3 (491– 493)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202639/files/figure.png" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Figs 493</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C61BFFEA2ED09906361B7F0C" box="[1243,1289,1620,1645]" captionStart="FIGURES 498–505" captionStartId="115.[151,264,1833,1855]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,195,1809]" captionTargetId="figure@115.[151,1436,193,1812]" captionTargetPageId="115" captionText="FIGURES 498–505. Mesabolivar constrictus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19208). 498, 500. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 499. Left procursus, dorsal view. 501–504. Epigynum, ventral, posterior, frontal, and lateral views. 505. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines:0.3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202643/files/figure.png" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">500</figureCitation>
), and by pair of epigynal processes only weakly curved backwards (compare 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C61BFFEA2969992530D47FF1" box="[866,966,1655,1680]" captionStart="FIGURES 494–497" captionStartId="113.[151,264,1248,1270]" captionTargetBox="[183,1408,207,1218]" captionTargetId="figure@113.[151,1436,193,1227]" captionTargetPageId="113" captionText="FIGURES 494–497. Mesabolivar saci sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19207). 494–496. Epigynum, ventral, lateral, and frontal views. 497. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines:0.3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202641/files/figure.png" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Figs 495</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C61BFFEA29DA992530ED7FF1" box="[977,1023,1655,1680]" captionStart="FIGURES 498–505" captionStartId="115.[151,264,1833,1855]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,195,1809]" captionTargetId="figure@115.[151,1436,193,1812]" captionTargetPageId="115" captionText="FIGURES 498–505. Mesabolivar constrictus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19208). 498, 500. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 499. Left procursus, dorsal view. 501–504. Epigynum, ventral, posterior, frontal, and lateral views. 505. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines:0.3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202643/files/figure.png" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">504</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D6B9258EC61BFFEA2ACC99CE31AB7FB9" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="9E1C7605C61BFFEA2ACC99CE31AB7FB9" blockId="111.[151,1437,1476,2005]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C61BFFEA2ACC99CE325C7FD4" bold="true" box="[199,334,1692,1717]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named for a character in Brazilian folklore (Saci) who grants wishes to anyone who manages to trap him (I did!); noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
